and everyone can--.

00:11:12.029 --> 00:11:13.939
Everyone hangs out and rolls them together.

00:11:13.939 --> 00:11:17.649
And that's a really cool way to get people
together.

00:11:17.649 --> 00:11:22.239
To get them interacting with their food, you
can do the same thing with a sushi party.

00:11:22.239 --> 00:11:29.199
So, the base of Vietnamese spring roll is
these things.

00:11:29.199 --> 00:11:31.949
And these can be found at most Whole Foods
stores.

00:11:31.949 --> 00:11:36.050
I don't know the Los Angeles grocery store
scene very well.

00:11:36.050 --> 00:11:40.489
So I'm not sure if you can get this at something
like Ralph's but definitely Whole Foods.

00:11:40.489 --> 00:11:42.399
Any sort of--.

00:11:42.399 --> 00:11:48.060
Definitely any Asian grocery supply store.

00:11:48.060 --> 00:11:52.410
And I would say probably most organic focused
health foods stores carry these.

00:11:52.410 --> 00:11:57.829
They're like a dollar ninety nine at most
for a package of 30 or 40.

00:11:57.829 --> 00:12:01.779
And they're basically just rice, really fine
ground rice, and water.

00:12:01.779 --> 00:12:06.220
So, fillings I am going to be using today
are vegetarian.

00:12:06.220 --> 00:12:12.600
But the possibilities are limitless when it
comes to Vietnamese spring rolls.

00:12:12.600 --> 00:12:14.119
You could add--.

00:12:14.119 --> 00:12:16.499
I've done it with grilled chicken and avocado
before.

00:12:16.499 --> 00:12:21.670
I do a really nice one with raw salmon and
mango and some fresh mint.

00:12:21.670 --> 00:12:23.170
That's really delicious.

00:12:23.170 --> 00:12:28.059
You can go more of a traditional route and
do grilled pork and shrimp.

00:12:28.059 --> 00:12:29.160
That's great.

00:12:29.160 --> 00:12:32.050
Avocado's always really good.

00:12:32.050 --> 00:12:36.529
Today I'm just going to be doing some really
basic vegetables and that helps keep it inexpensive.

00:12:36.529 --> 00:12:39.170
Makes a really nice lunch.

00:12:39.170 --> 00:12:44.009
So, it takes a little practice to figure out
how to do this.

00:12:44.009 --> 00:12:47.490
But once you get it, it's really not that
hard.

00:12:47.490 --> 00:12:54.509
You wanna dip this disk of rice stuff into
lukewarm water.

00:12:54.509 --> 00:12:57.749
You don't want it to be too hot or then it
will just fall apart in your hands.

00:12:57.749 --> 00:13:00.879
So, you can see it's already starting to become
more pliable.

00:13:00.879 --> 00:13:04.869
So I'm just gonna set it down on a clean dry
surface.

00:13:04.869 --> 00:13:10.610
And on the bottom, I'm gonna put some fresh
mint leaves.

00:13:10.610 --> 00:13:17.189
And it creates sort of a stained glass look
by pressing them, placing them face down like

00:13:17.189 --> 00:13:19.449
this so that they're facing out.

00:13:19.449 --> 00:13:21.730
So go like that.

00:13:21.730 --> 00:13:27.910
