00:33:30.020 --> 00:33:35.720
Because even if you don't get the discount,
usually you have to have a business I.D. number

00:33:35.720 --> 00:33:37.230
to get a full discount.

00:33:37.230 --> 00:33:44.070
But even if you don't get the discount, you’re
still gonna be able to find the products there

00:33:44.070 --> 00:33:50.110
for a whole lot less money than if you were
buying them at Sur La Table or something like

00:33:50.110 --> 00:33:51.110
that.

00:33:51.110 --> 00:33:56.860
&gt;&gt; male #9: If you've taught a lot of beginners,
you must have seen some of the same mistakes

00:33:56.860 --> 00:33:57.860
over and over again.

00:33:57.860 --> 00:33:59.600
Can you help us avoid those pitfalls?

00:33:59.600 --> 00:34:02.630
&gt;&gt; Gabi Moskowitz: Sure, sure.

00:34:02.630 --> 00:34:09.950
Well a really important thing is, whenever
you're working with hot chilies, wash your

00:34:09.950 --> 00:34:11.210
hands.

00:34:11.210 --> 00:34:17.069
Or if you're working with the veins, these
are red bell peppers, but you can even see

00:34:17.069 --> 00:34:20.869
here, all peppers have this white vein.

00:34:20.869 --> 00:34:23.070
Don't touch it with your hands if you can
avoid it.

00:34:23.070 --> 00:34:29.639
And definitely don't touch your girlfriend
with your hands after you touch it.

00:34:29.639 --> 00:34:33.169
So, that's really important.

00:34:33.169 --> 00:34:38.070
Really the number one thing, the number one
thing that gets people in trouble in the kitchen

00:34:38.070 --> 00:34:39.339
is a lack of confidence.

00:34:39.339 --> 00:34:41.179
They get all bogged down.

00:34:41.179 --> 00:34:46.109
You don't see people in the kitchen just blazing
forward.

00:34:46.109 --> 00:34:48.200
Very rare to see that kind of thing.

00:34:48.200 --> 00:34:49.200
It's more--.

00:34:49.200 --> 00:34:52.259
It more tends to be that people feel like
they can't do something.

00:34:52.259 --> 00:34:55.819
So, they reread the recipe a hundred times.

00:34:55.819 --> 00:35:02.170
And while that's happening their sauce burns
or something like that.

00:35:02.170 --> 00:35:06.220
Or really it's OK, but people feel like it's
not.

00:35:06.220 --> 00:35:13.380
So, there are, like I was saying before, there
are solutions out there that are really readily

00:35:13.380 --> 00:35:17.210
available for most common kitchen problems.

00:35:17.210 --> 00:35:22.400
But the number one solution is to know that
if you're working with--.

00:35:22.400 --> 00:35:25.869
This is not brain surgery.

00:35:25.869 --> 00:35:32.161
If you're working with fresh ingredients and
you're not trying to flambé everything, it's

00:35:32.161 --> 00:35:33.970
probably gonna turn out pretty well.

00:35:33.970 --> 00:35:37.549
And if it doesn't, you're the only one who
is gonna know.

00:35:37.549 --> 00:35:40.850
So, just accept the compliments when they
come.

00:35:40.850 --> 00:35:46.970
But yeah, I can't really think of anything
that's like a major no-no that people do all

00:35:46.970 --> 00:35:47.970
the time.

00:35:47.970 --> 00:35:56.119
I've seen kinds of silly things like, I had
a roommate who refrigerated red wine because

00:35:56.119 --> 00:35:58.410
she thought it goes bad.

00:35:58.410 --> 00:36:06.650
So, I had to explain it's fermented and it's
not gonna go bad.

00:36:06.650 --> 00:36:13.170
I guess a really common kitchen mistake is,
and it's really a financial mistake also,

00:36:13.170 --> 00:36:18.079
is that people let their food particularly
in their vegetable bin go bad.

00:36:18.079 --> 00:36:23.980
And if you, it happens a lot when people have
a CSA box and don't really go through and

00:36:23.980 --> 00:36:25.470
use everything regularly.

00:36:25.470 --> 00:36:29.900
And that's just basically taking money and
putting it in the compost bin.

00:36:29.900 --> 00:36:36.569
So, I really advise people to only buy what
they're gonna use and really make a point

00:36:36.569 --> 00:36:37.569
to use it.

